<TITLE> England complete 3-0 whitewash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 5 (bdnews24.com)  England completed a three-nil whitewash in the Beximco series after winning the third and final ODI against Bangladesh by 45 runs at the Zohur Ahmed Chowdhury Stadium in Chittagong on Friday. The Tigers never came to grips with the 285-run target as the top-order all made starts but ended their chase on 239-9 in 50 overs. Aftab Ahmed was top-scorer with 46 and he featured in a 56-run third wicket stand with Mushfiqur Rahim who was later out for a well-made 43-ball 40. The hosts made a disastrous start losing both openers, Tamim Iqbal for a duck and Imrul Kayes (17), inside the first 10 overs. Bangladesh fell further behind when skipper Shakib Al Hasan was adjudged leg-before-wicket to Kevin Pietersen for a run-a-ball 38, but TV replays showed he was hit outside the line. The ball also would have missed the stumps by a good few inches. Any hopes of a late charge ended with the dismissal of Mahmudullah (34) to leave them on 224-7 after 46 overs. Paceman Tim Bresnan was the pick of English bowlers with four for 28. Earlier, a maiden century from man of the match Craig Kieswetter helped England, who already clinched the series, to make an impressive 284-5 in 50 overs after being put into bat. The right-handed opener slammed 107 off 123 balls with nine fours and three sixes. Paul Collingwood and Eoin Morgan both made 36 while Luke Wright remained not out 32 off just 13 balls and skipper Alastair Cook also scored 32. Morgan was later named man of the se
